1
00:00:00,080 --> 00:00:02,016
(Previously) Why did you bring Boston in
to work with you?

2
00:00:02,040 --> 00:00:03,360
He nailed and bailed on Tua.

3
00:00:03,920 --> 00:00:05,040
I want to start over.

4
00:00:05,520 --> 00:00:06,760
It'd be nice to do it with you.

5
00:00:07,200 --> 00:00:09,840
Next time you see him, give me a signal.
I'll be your human shield.

6
00:00:10,040 --> 00:00:11,040
Poor thing.

7
00:00:11,480 --> 00:00:12,520
You decided to audition,

8
00:00:12,760 --> 00:00:14,216
and all you got was a supporting role.

9
00:00:14,240 --> 00:00:16,160
Just don't fall.
Or I will step right on you.

10
00:00:19,680 --> 00:00:21,216
You're the one
who leaked the news about Dean?

11
00:00:21,240 --> 00:00:22,240
Anyone could've done it.

12
00:00:22,760 --> 00:00:24,360
It's not just me who knows about it.

13
00:00:24,840 --> 00:00:27,560
Seeing you hurt… hurts me too.

14
00:00:34,200 --> 00:00:35,700
(Episode 4: Have fun, no drama)

15
00:00:41,440 --> 00:00:44,360
Whoo-hoo!

16
00:00:51,920 --> 00:00:53,400
Whoo-hoo!

17
00:01:00,760 --> 00:01:04,280
Whoo-hoo!

18
00:01:12,080 --> 00:01:13,080
Hey.

19
00:01:13,960 --> 00:01:14,960
What are you doing here?

20
00:01:15,480 --> 00:01:17,040
I'm bored. Let's go have fun.

21
00:01:17,640 --> 00:01:19,320
I'm working. Just leave for now.

22
00:01:24,960 --> 00:01:25,960
Hey!

23
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:27,000
What the hell?

24
00:01:27,001 --> 00:01:28,936
What are you doing?
We're in the middle of the club.

25
00:01:28,960 --> 00:01:29,960
So?

26
00:01:30,480 --> 00:01:31,480
I don't care.

27
00:01:31,560 --> 00:01:33,200
You like doing it out in the open, right?

28
00:01:33,560 --> 00:01:34,600
You should care sometimes.

29
00:01:35,920 --> 00:01:36,920
You can't do this.

30
00:01:38,400 --> 00:01:40,440
Didn't you say you'd be ready
whenever I wanted?

31
00:01:41,120 --> 00:01:42,320
I want you now.

32
00:01:43,800 --> 00:01:44,800
Gosh.

33
00:01:45,520 --> 00:01:46,840
What are you doing?!

34
00:01:47,800 --> 00:01:49,080
What the hell is wrong with you?

35
00:01:49,400 --> 00:01:50,400
Watch the booth for me.

36
00:01:50,600 --> 00:01:51,640
You. Step outside with me.

37
00:01:57,840 --> 00:01:58,480
Come here.
Ow! Where are you taking me?

38
00:01:59,480 --> 00:02:00,160
- Ow! Where are you taking me?
- Here!

39
00:02:00,480 --> 00:02:02,840
Ouch! That hurts!

40
00:02:03,160 --> 00:02:04,440
What the fuck is wrong with you?

41
00:02:04,480 --> 00:02:06,000
Are you here to fish for info from me?

42
00:02:06,120 --> 00:02:07,599
I'm not fishing for anything.

43
00:02:07,600 --> 00:02:08,600
You tricked me.

44
00:02:11,880 --> 00:02:13,320
You don't want it now, right?

45
00:02:14,240 --> 00:02:15,840
Fine. I'm okay.

46
00:02:16,880 --> 00:02:18,280
Didn't you already do it with Jack?

47
00:02:18,440 --> 00:02:20,360
How was it? You happy now?

48
00:02:20,720 --> 00:02:21,720
Jack's an idiot!

49
00:02:21,920 --> 00:02:23,600
He's back with that asshole Dean, damn it!

50
00:02:25,440 --> 00:02:26,080
See?

51
00:02:26,440 --> 00:02:27,440
Damn!

52
00:02:27,520 --> 00:02:28,520
What did I tell you?

53
00:02:28,720 --> 00:02:29,120
Huh?

54
00:02:29,520 --> 00:02:31,880
No matter how hard you try,
he'll never want you.

55
00:02:33,160 --> 00:02:35,480
Yeah, no one ever wants me.

56
00:02:38,360 --> 00:02:42,119
Hey, boy. Why don't you come with me?

57
00:02:42,120 --> 00:02:43,279
Are you drunk, bro?

58
00:02:43,280 --> 00:02:44,919
No, I'm not.

59
00:02:44,920 --> 00:02:46,039
You can come with me.

60
00:02:46,040 --> 00:02:47,199
I'm fine. It's okay.

61
00:02:47,200 --> 00:02:49,319
I'm not drunk.
You can go home with me, seriously.

62
00:02:49,320 --> 00:02:50,519
I think I'm fine.

63
00:02:50,520 --> 00:02:51,200
I can do anything.
No, thank you.

64
00:02:51,721 --> 00:02:53,120
Sorry. My friend's wasted.

65
00:02:53,240 --> 00:02:54,840
Friend, my ass.

66
00:02:55,120 --> 00:02:55,680
Let go of me!

67
00:02:55,681 --> 00:02:56,720
Hell no.

68
00:02:56,840 --> 00:02:58,080
Why are you grabbing me?

69
00:02:58,400 --> 00:02:59,680
What the fuck is wrong with you?

70
00:02:59,760 --> 00:03:01,200
Didn't you say you only wanted Jack?

71
00:03:01,880 --> 00:03:02,680
Let me go!
No.

72
00:03:04,840 --> 00:03:07,200
Tonight, I'm going fucking wild!

73
00:03:08,440 --> 00:03:10,320
Fine. You want it wild?

74
00:03:10,560 --> 00:03:13,040
Then be wild with me.

75
00:03:13,312 --> 00:03:14,472
Ow. Let go of me.

76
00:03:15,360 --> 00:03:16,360
Let go!

77
00:05:20,200 --> 00:05:21,200
Hello.

78
00:05:21,240 --> 00:05:22,240
(Open the door for me.)

79
00:05:22,360 --> 00:05:23,400
(I'm outside your studio.)

80
00:05:39,200 --> 00:05:41,200
Make yourself comfortable.
I'll grab you a beer.

81
00:05:42,240 --> 00:05:43,240
No need.

82
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:44,840
I'll say it quick.
Then I'll leave.

83
00:05:46,560 --> 00:05:47,560
Alright then.

84
00:05:48,600 --> 00:05:49,600
What's up?

85
00:05:53,400 --> 00:05:55,240
Drop out as
the behind-the-scenes photographer.

86
00:05:58,240 --> 00:06:00,440
Done. I'll drop out.

87
00:06:03,520 --> 00:06:07,120
But you'll have to tell Jack yourself
why you want me out.

88
00:06:08,160 --> 00:06:09,240
Um…

89
00:06:09,720 --> 00:06:10,880
What should be the reason?

90
00:06:13,800 --> 00:06:14,800
Ah!

91
00:06:15,920 --> 00:06:17,120
You and I hooked up.

92
00:06:17,560 --> 00:06:20,480
You got attached. And what else?

93
00:06:22,400 --> 00:06:23,720
What exactly do you want, Boston?

94
00:06:39,840 --> 00:06:41,080
I want to go after you.

95
00:06:44,560 --> 00:06:47,480
The day I wanted you,
you chose someone else.

96
00:06:48,280 --> 00:06:51,400
Now that you want me,
you just walk in and demand it?

97
00:06:52,120 --> 00:06:54,400
Well, if you're really single,
I truly want to pursue you.

98
00:06:55,720 --> 00:06:57,200
Back then, I didn't want commitment.

99
00:06:59,400 --> 00:07:00,400
But now…

100
00:07:04,360 --> 00:07:05,360
I do.

101
00:07:06,760 --> 00:07:07,760
No.

102
00:07:09,520 --> 00:07:10,520
Why not?

103
00:07:11,680 --> 00:07:13,320
Are you waiting to get with Arnold first?

104
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:16,040
That's my business.

105
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:18,480
Why do you have to get involved?

106
00:07:19,640 --> 00:07:20,640
Suit yourself.

107
00:07:22,160 --> 00:07:23,160
But I mean it.

108
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:24,600
I can wait.

109
00:07:47,840 --> 00:07:49,000
I miss the old days.

110
00:07:50,120 --> 00:07:54,279
We were together almost twenty-four.

111
00:07:54,280 --> 00:07:57,759
We'd rehearse until the theater closed
and the security guard kicked us out.

112
00:07:57,760 --> 00:08:00,080
Then we'd keep rehearsing
on the rooftop of your apartment.

113
00:08:12,200 --> 00:08:18,360
Do you think we could
ever go back to how we were?

114
00:08:20,040 --> 00:08:21,200
Are you serious?

115
00:08:23,680 --> 00:08:29,080
I just want to know
if we'll ever get back together.

116
00:08:37,720 --> 00:08:38,960
I don't know, Dean.

117
00:08:40,720 --> 00:08:44,640
I think a lot has changed.

118
00:08:46,440 --> 00:08:49,520
This new me isn't the same as the old me.

119
00:08:51,680 --> 00:08:55,480
Is it really that hard to
just answer yes or no?

120
00:08:56,480 --> 00:09:00,360
Dean, you and I are both headstrong.

121
00:09:00,760 --> 00:09:05,160
Maybe it's better for us to
stay friends like this than be boyfriends.

122
00:09:05,720 --> 00:09:08,839
No. I liked it better
when we were boyfriends.

123
00:09:08,840 --> 00:09:10,000
Better than being friends.

124
00:09:10,440 --> 00:09:11,440
That's not true.

125
00:09:12,520 --> 00:09:14,360
When we were dating, I was unreasonable.

126
00:09:14,720 --> 00:09:17,880
I got possessive and jealous.
We ended up fighting all the time.

127
00:09:30,520 --> 00:09:31,520
How about this?

128
00:09:31,760 --> 00:09:37,200
Of all the things you asked me,
I can grant you one.

129
00:09:51,440 --> 00:09:55,280
UNBLOCK DEAN_DECHAKORN?

130
00:10:02,960 --> 00:10:05,840
Right now, this is all I can do for you.

131
00:10:08,040 --> 00:10:09,040
Fair enough.

132
00:10:09,480 --> 00:10:13,560
At least right now, I'm one step closer.

133
00:10:22,400 --> 00:10:23,400
Hey, Jack.

134
00:10:26,880 --> 00:10:28,440
I'll be the new Dean for you.

135
00:10:32,360 --> 00:10:33,360
Dean.

136
00:10:33,760 --> 00:10:36,040
That's not right. That's the old Dean.

137
00:10:37,120 --> 00:10:38,280
Just wait and see.

138
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:40,480
I'm going to be the new Dean for you.

139
00:10:43,760 --> 00:10:45,760
I'm going to be the new Dean!

140
00:10:52,520 --> 00:10:53,520
I'll show you.

141
00:10:54,360 --> 00:10:55,480
This time, it's for real.

142
00:10:57,560 --> 00:10:58,800
I'll wait and see.

143
00:11:35,080 --> 00:11:36,080
Watch it.

144
00:11:45,320 --> 00:11:46,320
Thank you.

145
00:11:48,040 --> 00:11:49,200
We almost caused a scene.

146
00:11:50,840 --> 00:11:53,600
You were right to ask me to come help.

147
00:11:53,840 --> 00:11:54,840
Here.

148
00:11:57,280 --> 00:11:58,280
The orange one?

149
00:11:58,680 --> 00:11:59,680
Mm.

150
00:12:00,920 --> 00:12:02,560
I'm the one who knows you best.

151
00:12:06,840 --> 00:12:08,360
Hey, Arnold.

152
00:12:10,360 --> 00:12:11,360
Irene?

153
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:12,400
Hi.

154
00:12:12,960 --> 00:12:14,120
Surprised to see you here.

155
00:12:14,480 --> 00:12:17,000
Mm. I'm helping my friend
pick up some things.

156
00:12:17,560 --> 00:12:18,920
He's making costumes for the play.

157
00:12:19,200 --> 00:12:21,360
Ah, the one you're acting in, right?

158
00:12:23,640 --> 00:12:25,120
You're really leveling up these days.

159
00:12:25,480 --> 00:12:26,680
You can do so many things now.

160
00:12:27,560 --> 00:12:29,920
I'm rooting for you. I'll
come watch your play.

161
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:32,600
Okay. I'll see you around.

162
00:12:34,280 --> 00:12:35,280
Bye-bye.

163
00:12:50,360 --> 00:12:51,360
Was that your friend?

164
00:12:53,640 --> 00:12:55,160
Uh… friend?

165
00:12:55,600 --> 00:12:56,600
Not exactly.

166
00:12:57,360 --> 00:12:58,440
I'm not sure how to put it.

167
00:13:00,880 --> 00:13:01,880
Care to explain?

168
00:13:03,040 --> 00:13:05,840
We were very close back in high school.

169
00:13:06,440 --> 00:13:08,400
But before graduation,
she confessed she liked me.

170
00:13:08,960 --> 00:13:10,240
I didn't respond.

171
00:13:10,640 --> 00:13:12,320
That's why it's kind of awkward.

172
00:13:13,200 --> 00:13:16,360
Shit. That's exactly why
I never bring friends to the talking stage.

173
00:13:18,600 --> 00:13:19,720
Not a single case ends well.

174
00:13:21,033 --> 00:13:24,393
Hey, but that doesn't happen to everyone.

175
00:13:25,400 --> 00:13:28,320
Really? From what I've seen,
everyone has this problem.

176
00:13:28,677 --> 00:13:31,480
Like her and me. Or Jack and Dean.

177
00:13:33,080 --> 00:13:36,600
In this lifetime, I'm
never dating a friend.

178
00:13:37,080 --> 00:13:38,760
Breaking up with a partner is one thing.

179
00:13:39,040 --> 00:13:42,080
Breaking up with a friend… hurts even worse.

180
00:13:49,480 --> 00:13:50,480
Yes, sir.

181
00:13:51,480 --> 00:13:52,160
Thank you.

182
00:13:52,161 --> 00:13:53,439
Can you please grab that?

183
00:13:53,440 --> 00:13:54,440
Sure.

184
00:14:01,880 --> 00:14:03,880
It's like I just got indirectly rejected.

185
00:14:15,480 --> 00:14:16,480
You're up?

186
00:14:21,760 --> 00:14:22,880
How did I end up here?

187
00:14:25,240 --> 00:14:27,336
You were such a troublemaker last night,
you know that?

188
00:14:27,360 --> 00:14:28,440
And you're heavy as hell.

189
00:14:29,760 --> 00:14:31,440
So how did I end up coming home with you?

190
00:14:33,680 --> 00:14:34,759
Because I didn't want you waking up

191
00:14:34,760 --> 00:14:37,800
regretting you slept with
someone less hot than me.

192
00:14:40,720 --> 00:14:41,720
Gosh.

193
00:14:45,520 --> 00:14:46,520
That's my tee.

194
00:14:47,960 --> 00:14:49,920
We didn't do anything last night, though.

195
00:14:50,800 --> 00:14:52,776
I don't sleep with drunk people,
especially the troublemaking kind.

196
00:14:52,800 --> 00:14:53,800
Come on.

197
00:14:54,400 --> 00:14:57,080
Don't yell at me first thing in
the morning. I'm not ready for that.

198
00:15:00,680 --> 00:15:01,680
Here.

199
00:15:05,280 --> 00:15:06,840
Have some coffee first.

200
00:15:09,440 --> 00:15:10,960
My head is killing me.

201
00:15:22,840 --> 00:15:24,400
You're really passionate about music.

202
00:15:26,600 --> 00:15:27,600
I told you.

203
00:15:28,280 --> 00:15:31,360
I'm soon to be a world-class DJ.

204
00:15:32,160 --> 00:15:33,160
Someone's confident.

205
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:35,600
How about you hit 100K subscribers first?

206
00:15:39,800 --> 00:15:42,640
For stuff like this,
you must take one step at a time.

207
00:15:43,880 --> 00:15:48,320
On days you miss me,
you can play my playlists.

208
00:15:53,800 --> 00:15:54,800
No need.

209
00:15:55,640 --> 00:15:56,920
Because I won't miss you.

210
00:15:57,240 --> 00:15:59,240
Hm. Smart mouth.

211
00:16:01,560 --> 00:16:02,560
Here.

212
00:16:03,080 --> 00:16:04,080
Your breakfast.

213
00:16:04,480 --> 00:16:06,040
Sleep with me, free breakfast.

214
00:16:38,040 --> 00:16:40,200
Hey, here comes the host.

215
00:16:40,440 --> 00:16:42,160
Hi, James Dean.

216
00:16:42,320 --> 00:16:43,320
Jeez!

217
00:16:43,920 --> 00:16:47,559
I heard that he got paid 10K
just to eat and drink.

218
00:16:47,560 --> 00:16:47,840
That's a lot.

219
00:16:47,841 --> 00:16:50,040
- Should I do it too?
- Yes, you should.

220
00:16:52,080 --> 00:16:53,080
Hold this.

221
00:17:00,520 --> 00:17:01,520
So?

222
00:17:01,680 --> 00:17:03,760
Yeah, I'm James Dean.

223
00:17:04,272 --> 00:17:06,632
The VIP host you've been gossiping about.

224
00:17:08,541 --> 00:17:10,280
Hey, you dare to hire me?

225
00:17:10,680 --> 00:17:13,840
If you do, I'll entertain you too.

226
00:17:16,160 --> 00:17:20,040
And my rate is 15K, not just 10K.

227
00:17:20,440 --> 00:17:23,120
No need to ask why I had to do this job.

228
00:17:24,240 --> 00:17:25,600
Because I'm not rich like you are.

229
00:17:26,520 --> 00:17:31,039
I had to work an honest job
to support my family and myself

230
00:17:31,040 --> 00:17:32,720
so I could study at the same place as you.

231
00:17:34,400 --> 00:17:37,400
If you have more
questions, feel free to ask.

232
00:17:37,593 --> 00:17:40,713
I'm right here to answer.
Stop spreading nonsense behind my back.

233
00:17:51,760 --> 00:17:53,320
As for the one who tried to step on me,

234
00:17:56,440 --> 00:18:00,200
congratulations on leaking the news.

235
00:18:01,200 --> 00:18:06,760
But sorry, this crap can't hurt me.

236
00:18:11,640 --> 00:18:14,760
Stop staring and keep your noses
out of other people's business.

237
00:18:17,120 --> 00:18:18,320
Worry about your own lives.

238
00:18:19,480 --> 00:18:20,480
No more drama.

239
00:18:28,000 --> 00:18:29,320
You finally got over it.

240
00:18:29,920 --> 00:18:31,576
I thought you'd hide
it for the rest of your.

241
00:18:31,600 --> 00:18:31,920
Come.

242
00:18:32,560 --> 00:18:33,800
Let's go rehearse the play.

243
00:18:42,720 --> 00:18:43,720
He's cool.

244
00:18:44,480 --> 00:18:47,440
If it were me getting criticized like
that, I wouldn't dare show up at uni.

245
00:18:51,080 --> 00:18:52,280
Well, he had to face it.

246
00:18:53,120 --> 00:18:54,120
It's the truth.

247
00:19:01,880 --> 00:19:05,280
In the play, you're supposed to
look like you're in love.

248
00:19:08,080 --> 00:19:11,880
So you need to convey that feeling
to the audience. Okay?

249
00:19:12,200 --> 00:19:13,200
Mm.

250
00:19:14,960 --> 00:19:18,080
So today we're going to do a workshop.

251
00:19:21,040 --> 00:19:22,520
Face each other slowly.

252
00:19:25,920 --> 00:19:27,720
Relax and get comfortable.

253
00:19:30,040 --> 00:19:31,280
Slowly close your eyes.

254
00:19:39,440 --> 00:19:42,520
Imagine the person in front of you
is your loved one.

255
00:19:44,360 --> 00:19:47,480
Then slowly open your eyes.

256
00:19:49,720 --> 00:19:57,160
Take a good look at his face.
See if there's anything you like.

257
00:19:58,640 --> 00:20:00,240
Then slowly send your feeling…

258
00:20:04,200 --> 00:20:06,120
to the person in front of you
as much as you can.

259
00:20:18,040 --> 00:20:21,640
Once you feel it, slowly step forward
and hug each other.

260
00:20:33,360 --> 00:20:34,360
Right.

261
00:20:34,720 --> 00:20:35,720
Did you feel it, Arnold?

262
00:20:35,880 --> 00:20:38,240
Hey. Yeah, I felt a lot.

263
00:20:38,520 --> 00:20:39,520
That's great.

264
00:20:39,760 --> 00:20:40,360
Dean?

265
00:20:40,440 --> 00:20:42,200
Yeah, I felt it too.

266
00:20:43,320 --> 00:20:44,719
Okay, that worked.

267
00:20:44,720 --> 00:20:46,919
Try to hold on to that feeling.

268
00:20:46,920 --> 00:20:48,960
Guys, let's rehearse the first scene.

269
00:20:49,760 --> 00:20:50,760
Turn to page one.

270
00:20:53,600 --> 00:20:54,800
Dean, Arnold, sit over here.

271
00:21:03,080 --> 00:21:04,800
Arnold and Dean have amazing chemistry.

272
00:21:06,280 --> 00:21:07,280
Aren't you scared?

273
00:21:09,640 --> 00:21:12,160
They're lovers in the play.
Of course, they need good chemistry.

274
00:21:24,520 --> 00:21:26,160
Want to grab something to eat after this?

275
00:21:28,560 --> 00:21:29,560
I don't have time.

276
00:21:29,800 --> 00:21:31,040
I have to work on the costumes.

277
00:21:32,840 --> 00:21:34,680
We can go to the same place we first met.

278
00:21:35,680 --> 00:21:36,760
I'll take care of you.

279
00:21:38,760 --> 00:21:42,280
But if you don't like crowded
places, my house is free.

280
00:22:00,880 --> 00:22:01,600
Yes, Mom.

281
00:22:01,800 --> 00:22:02,800
I'm on my way.

282
00:22:02,960 --> 00:22:05,640
The traffic shouldn't be too bad.
I should be there in half an hour.

283
00:22:07,800 --> 00:22:08,800
Of course.

284
00:22:09,160 --> 00:22:10,160
See you later, Mom.

285
00:22:52,240 --> 00:22:53,520
Your engine doesn't sound right.

286
00:22:53,640 --> 00:22:54,640
Is it broken?

287
00:22:56,200 --> 00:22:57,320
I think so.

288
00:22:58,400 --> 00:23:00,160
Where are you going? Want a ride?

289
00:23:03,480 --> 00:23:04,480
No.

290
00:23:04,680 --> 00:23:05,960
I'll call my driver.

291
00:23:17,600 --> 00:23:18,600
Hi, Uncle Pong.

292
00:23:19,720 --> 00:23:22,880
My car broke down.
Can you pick me up at the uni?

293
00:23:26,200 --> 00:23:27,720
Ah…

294
00:23:29,560 --> 00:23:31,200
You're at the car wash with my mom's car?

295
00:23:32,720 --> 00:23:35,320
Alright then.

296
00:23:35,633 --> 00:23:36,633
Goodbye.

297
00:23:39,400 --> 00:23:40,560
Well, young master?

298
00:23:41,360 --> 00:23:43,040
Coming with me or taking a motorbike taxi?

299
00:23:58,200 --> 00:23:59,200
So, where are you going?

300
00:24:00,520 --> 00:24:01,520
Hey!

301
00:24:05,120 --> 00:24:08,520
Well, I usually sit in the back
when there's a driver.

302
00:24:08,720 --> 00:24:09,800
Oh, wow.

303
00:24:10,480 --> 00:24:12,440
Are you seriously
treating me like your chauffeur?

304
00:24:16,440 --> 00:24:18,360
Drive safe, Mr. Chauffeur.

305
00:24:21,280 --> 00:24:22,680
I've already sent you the location.

306
00:24:25,760 --> 00:24:27,136
Give you an inch and you take a mile.

307
00:24:27,160 --> 00:24:28,160
Mm.

308
00:24:28,440 --> 00:24:29,440
Okay.

309
00:24:30,120 --> 00:24:33,440
Then this chauffeur will do his best,
young master.

310
00:24:34,440 --> 00:24:35,440
Just sit tight.

311
00:24:36,040 --> 00:24:37,840
Don't go crying to mommy
if you hit your head.

312
00:24:38,240 --> 00:24:39,240
You asshole.

313
00:24:56,000 --> 00:24:57,680
Are you really not coming with me?

314
00:24:58,480 --> 00:25:00,480
You said you wanted to
talk to me about the script.

315
00:25:01,840 --> 00:25:05,520
I have an audition.
Don't you want to come cheer me on?

316
00:25:06,960 --> 00:25:08,680
You should ask Tua and Timmy.

317
00:25:09,600 --> 00:25:11,040
They're not available.

318
00:25:12,000 --> 00:25:13,040
So now it's down to you.

319
00:25:15,120 --> 00:25:19,280
It's fine if you don't come. If I
don't get the part, I'll just cry alone.

320
00:25:19,600 --> 00:25:21,279
You don't care anyway.

321
00:25:21,280 --> 00:25:25,280
Even though you know I'd feel
more confident if someone came with me.

322
00:25:26,440 --> 00:25:27,440
Hey.

323
00:25:28,640 --> 00:25:29,640
What?

324
00:25:30,040 --> 00:25:31,480
Why are you so dramatic?

325
00:25:33,400 --> 00:25:36,320
Don't come.
Just wait here and comfort me after.

326
00:25:38,200 --> 00:25:39,200
Alright!

327
00:25:40,720 --> 00:25:41,720
I'll come.

328
00:25:44,200 --> 00:25:46,440
But I'll come as your
friend, not boyfriend.

329
00:25:49,800 --> 00:25:50,800
Sure thing.

330
00:25:52,160 --> 00:25:54,199
I'll show you different
versions on the way,

331
00:25:54,200 --> 00:25:56,400
and you can tell me which one's best.
Sound good?

332
00:25:56,960 --> 00:25:58,400
So we're taking my car?

333
00:25:59,160 --> 00:26:00,480
Just like old times.

334
00:26:00,800 --> 00:26:01,959
You drive and I'll navigate.

335
00:26:01,960 --> 00:26:02,960
Yeah?

336
00:26:07,800 --> 00:26:08,280
Hi, Mom.

337
00:26:08,480 --> 00:26:10,560
(I haven't heard from you lately.)

338
00:26:11,040 --> 00:26:13,280
(Was the money I sent you enough?)

339
00:26:13,520 --> 00:26:14,520
It was, Mom.

340
00:26:15,440 --> 00:26:18,640
I've got classes and part-time jobs.
Kind of swamped.

341
00:26:19,400 --> 00:26:23,840
Oh, hey. I'm in the faculty play.
I even got paid.

342
00:26:24,560 --> 00:26:26,176
I'll send you some photos
so you can see them in LA.

343
00:26:26,200 --> 00:26:29,520
(Mm. Don't forget to
take some time to rest, son.)

344
00:26:29,760 --> 00:26:31,880
(Whatever it is,
you can always give me a call.)

345
00:26:32,040 --> 00:26:35,600
(If you have some problems,
you can call me anytime.)

346
00:26:35,760 --> 00:26:36,440
(Okay?)
Yes, Mom.

347
00:26:37,600 --> 00:26:38,720
I miss you.

348
00:26:39,160 --> 00:26:41,400
Say hi to Uncle Steve for me, okay?

349
00:26:42,000 --> 00:26:43,640
Okay. Love you, Mom.

350
00:26:53,360 --> 00:26:54,360
Arnold.

351
00:26:54,800 --> 00:26:55,480
Hey.

352
00:26:55,800 --> 00:26:56,800
You're still here?

353
00:26:56,960 --> 00:27:01,000
Yeah. Just finished a call with my mom
and was about to record a TikTok.

354
00:27:01,640 --> 00:27:04,440
What about you?
Can you do the move I taught you?

355
00:27:06,440 --> 00:27:08,079
I practiced a little.

356
00:27:08,080 --> 00:27:09,559
I think I can manage a bit.

357
00:27:09,560 --> 00:27:11,119
Hey, that's great. That's my friend.

358
00:27:11,120 --> 00:27:13,080
Let's try it now.

359
00:27:43,960 --> 00:27:44,640
Action.

360
00:27:44,641 --> 00:27:46,639
Tasty! One bite, and the crunch
stays with you forever.

361
00:27:46,640 --> 00:27:48,840
A new PIZZA flavor is out now.

362
00:27:48,960 --> 00:27:50,879
Tasty! One bite, and the crunch
stays with you forever.

363
00:27:50,880 --> 00:27:52,520
A new PIZZA flavor is out now.

364
00:27:52,960 --> 00:27:53,560
One more time, please.

365
00:27:53,561 --> 00:27:54,920
Make it more fun.

366
00:27:54,960 --> 00:27:55,960
Okay.

367
00:27:56,160 --> 00:27:57,879
Tasty! One bite, and the crunch
stays with you forever.

368
00:27:57,880 --> 00:27:59,479
A new PIZZA flavor is out now.

369
00:27:59,480 --> 00:28:01,400
So so good, I'm not even lying.

370
00:28:03,960 --> 00:28:04,960
Cut!

371
00:28:06,080 --> 00:28:07,599
That's good. I like it.

372
00:28:07,600 --> 00:28:09,280
If it works out, you'll get a call.

373
00:28:09,480 --> 00:28:10,480
Sure.

374
00:28:10,960 --> 00:28:11,720
Good luck.

375
00:28:11,721 --> 00:28:12,960
Thank you.

376
00:28:14,080 --> 00:28:15,679
I like it a lot.

377
00:28:15,680 --> 00:28:16,600
Get home safe.
Thank you.

378
00:28:17,560 --> 00:28:18,480
Come on. It's done.
How was it?

379
00:28:20,760 --> 00:28:22,800
I might get it. They said I did well.

380
00:28:23,600 --> 00:28:25,760
Should we go now? I have to edit my script.

381
00:28:26,280 --> 00:28:29,440
Let me run to the restroom for a second.
You can wait for me in the parking lot.

382
00:28:31,960 --> 00:28:34,679
I like Dean so much, but we can't pick him.

383
00:28:34,680 --> 00:28:37,560
Why not? He was so good.

384
00:28:37,960 --> 00:28:40,919
He hasn't hit 50k followers yet.

385
00:28:40,920 --> 00:28:43,160
The client won't say yes,
no matter how hard we push him.

386
00:28:43,240 --> 00:28:44,960
Gosh, what a shame.

387
00:28:45,600 --> 00:28:46,600
Come on.

388
00:28:48,200 --> 00:28:49,919
But he was so good just now.

389
00:28:49,920 --> 00:28:51,439
Chef's kiss.

390
00:28:51,440 --> 00:28:52,959
Right. His delivery was perfect.

391
00:28:52,960 --> 00:28:53,840
Did you see when he took a bite?
Yum.

392
00:29:12,160 --> 00:29:13,160
Hi, Mom.

393
00:29:14,200 --> 00:29:17,759
Gosh. I thought you
weren't going to make it.

394
00:29:17,760 --> 00:29:19,239
You took forever.

395
00:29:19,240 --> 00:29:21,960
Once you're in the industry,
you can't be like this.

396
00:29:23,400 --> 00:29:26,920
My car broke down. That's why I'm late.

397
00:29:27,440 --> 00:29:28,440
Yeah?

398
00:29:28,760 --> 00:29:29,840
So how did you get here?

399
00:29:32,400 --> 00:29:33,760
I booked a ride.

400
00:29:35,240 --> 00:29:36,240
Hello, ma'am.

401
00:29:36,360 --> 00:29:37,560
I'm Rome, Raffy's friend.

402
00:29:38,200 --> 00:29:39,200
Hello, there.

403
00:29:39,320 --> 00:29:42,040
Thanks for bringing our Little Raf here.

404
00:29:42,160 --> 00:29:44,800
I've been asking him to come.
I thought he was going to bail on me.

405
00:29:46,120 --> 00:29:47,120
Little Raf, huh?

406
00:29:53,960 --> 00:29:56,920
Are you going to shoot the show
with this outfit and hair?

407
00:29:57,440 --> 00:30:00,760
I had class earlier and
didn't have any other clothes with me.

408
00:30:01,120 --> 00:30:02,360
I don't think this will do.

409
00:30:02,640 --> 00:30:05,400
Good thing I told the staff
to prepare a costume for you.

410
00:30:05,560 --> 00:30:08,399
Please take Little Raf to get makeup done
and change into the new outfit.

411
00:30:08,400 --> 00:30:09,400
Of course.

412
00:30:09,840 --> 00:30:11,080
Little Raffy, this way, please.

413
00:30:18,480 --> 00:30:19,480
Thank you.

414
00:30:20,160 --> 00:30:21,160
This is amazing.

415
00:30:22,240 --> 00:30:23,960
I didn't know you liked Indian food.

416
00:30:25,280 --> 00:30:27,320
I've never tried it before.
This is my first time.

417
00:30:28,440 --> 00:30:30,000
I never paid attention to it either.

418
00:30:30,480 --> 00:30:33,960
But after coming to Little India often
to buy fabrics, I gave it a try.

419
00:30:34,240 --> 00:30:38,920
And I realized I'd been
missing out all my life.

420
00:30:39,800 --> 00:30:41,000
That good, huh?

421
00:30:42,720 --> 00:30:43,760
Guess I should try it too.

422
00:30:44,600 --> 00:30:45,880
- Can I go now?
- Go ahead.

423
00:30:46,880 --> 00:30:48,440
And take a bite.

424
00:30:49,000 --> 00:30:50,200
Come on, you barely dipped it.

425
00:30:52,680 --> 00:30:54,119
Mm.

426
00:30:54,120 --> 00:30:54,520
Good?
Mhm.

427
00:30:56,680 --> 00:30:59,280
Wow, it's really good.

428
00:31:03,880 --> 00:31:05,920
Come on. You eat like a kid.

429
00:31:06,640 --> 00:31:07,640
Here.

430
00:31:21,240 --> 00:31:22,240
Thank you.

431
00:31:30,120 --> 00:31:31,760
Why do you like making clothes, Tua?

432
00:31:35,680 --> 00:31:39,600
When I was a kid, I loved watching parades
at my family's amusement park.

433
00:31:40,280 --> 00:31:44,080
I thought the costumes were
cute, and I loved dressing up.

434
00:31:44,440 --> 00:31:45,440
What about you?

435
00:31:48,280 --> 00:31:49,760
Actually, I don't really know.

436
00:31:51,040 --> 00:31:53,760
I just do whatever makes me money.

437
00:31:55,240 --> 00:31:57,959
At first, I didn't feel anything special
about my jobs.

438
00:31:57,960 --> 00:32:01,080
But after a while, I started to enjoy them.

439
00:32:02,880 --> 00:32:03,880
Good.

440
00:32:04,320 --> 00:32:05,400
That's different from me.

441
00:32:06,840 --> 00:32:09,320
I'm lucky I don't have
to worry about money.

442
00:32:10,440 --> 00:32:12,080
I get to do what I like.

443
00:32:12,800 --> 00:32:14,480
Yeah, that's really different.

444
00:32:15,040 --> 00:32:17,680
Ever since my mom remarried
and moved to LA with her new husband,

445
00:32:18,120 --> 00:32:20,200
I've had to take on more jobs
to support myself.

446
00:32:20,920 --> 00:32:26,840
She sends me money,
but I don't want to burden her.

447
00:32:27,720 --> 00:32:28,920
Anyway, working is fun.

448
00:32:30,040 --> 00:32:31,640
I really admire you.

449
00:32:33,480 --> 00:32:34,920
Sometimes I can't help wondering

450
00:32:35,440 --> 00:32:39,080
if I'd have come this far
without my family's support.

451
00:32:39,720 --> 00:32:41,320
You're really amazing, Arnold.

452
00:32:42,400 --> 00:32:43,400
Thank you.

453
00:32:47,920 --> 00:32:48,920
Pass me a tissue.

454
00:32:56,000 --> 00:33:04,000
ARNOLD, WANNA MODEL
FOR A SHOOT FOR ME?

455
00:33:08,680 --> 00:33:12,959
UH… CAN I THINK ABOUT IT FIRST?

456
00:33:12,960 --> 00:33:14,800
YOU'LL GET PAID TOO.

457
00:33:18,560 --> 00:33:21,120
Tua, Boston just DMed me.

458
00:33:21,560 --> 00:33:23,440
He wants me to model
for a shoot at his studio.

459
00:33:23,920 --> 00:33:25,040
He'll pay me too.

460
00:33:27,560 --> 00:33:29,400
If you're not okay
with it, I can just not go.

461
00:33:32,720 --> 00:33:33,720
I'm okay.

462
00:33:34,920 --> 00:33:36,640
I don't think he's after anything with you.

463
00:33:37,240 --> 00:33:40,000
And whatever we had
ended a long time ago.

464
00:33:41,000 --> 00:33:42,000
Mm.

465
00:33:44,200 --> 00:33:45,200
Are you sure?

466
00:33:47,920 --> 00:33:48,920
I am.

467
00:33:51,360 --> 00:33:52,360
Okay.

468
00:34:04,160 --> 00:34:06,440
What exactly does Boston want from me?

469
00:34:13,760 --> 00:34:16,559
Now, let's talk about Miss Ran's son.

470
00:34:16,560 --> 00:34:19,840
I heard he showed potential as an actor
since he was young. Is that true, Miss Ran?

471
00:34:20,280 --> 00:34:23,519
Little Raf has always
been confident in front of people.

472
00:34:23,520 --> 00:34:29,599
I had him take acting, singing,
and music classes when he was little.

473
00:34:29,600 --> 00:34:32,399
Wow, he's very skillful.

474
00:34:32,400 --> 00:34:38,400
(Watch on www.dramacool.club Support Admin)

475
00:34:32,400 --> 00:34:33,479
What about you, Little Raf?

476
00:34:33,480 --> 00:34:35,919
Are you planning to
follow in your mom's footsteps

477
00:34:35,920 --> 00:34:37,600
and enter the entertainment industry?

478
00:34:42,960 --> 00:34:44,960
Uh, I am.

479
00:34:45,280 --> 00:34:50,359
If any producers are watching this,
feel free to contact me directly.

480
00:34:50,360 --> 00:34:52,759
Wow. You're his manager too, yes?

481
00:34:52,760 --> 00:34:57,359
He's a handsome young man, and
the son of Miss Ran, a top-tier actress.

482
00:34:57,360 --> 00:35:02,760
I'm sure we can look forward to
a new rising star in the industry.

483
00:35:04,640 --> 00:35:09,920
Lastly, Miss Ran, could you tell the audience
what projects they'll be seeing you in?

484
00:35:10,560 --> 00:35:12,279
I have a TV drama coming out
at the end of the year.

485
00:35:12,280 --> 00:35:17,959
But I'd also like to share that Little Raf
will be starring in his faculty play.

486
00:35:17,960 --> 00:35:20,399
He plays the lead role,
so please stay tuned for that.

487
00:35:20,400 --> 00:35:23,519
Wow, like mother, like son.

488
00:35:23,520 --> 00:35:29,039
Thank you so much today, Miss Ranchalee
and Little Raffy, for speaking with us.

489
00:35:29,040 --> 00:35:30,800
Until next time. Goodbye.

490
00:35:31,600 --> 00:35:32,600
Cut.

491
00:35:33,400 --> 00:35:34,879
Miss Ran, thank you so much again.

492
00:35:34,880 --> 00:35:36,999
It's truly my pleasure. Thank you so much.

493
00:35:37,000 --> 00:35:38,640
Can we get a photo, please?

494
00:35:39,040 --> 00:35:40,040
Of course.

495
00:35:41,000 --> 00:35:43,039
I've always been your fan.

496
00:35:43,040 --> 00:35:43,920
Thank you so much.

497
00:35:43,921 --> 00:35:45,880
And thank you for interviewing us.

498
00:35:47,840 --> 00:35:48,840
Looking good.

499
00:35:49,480 --> 00:35:50,200
Do you want a picture too?

500
00:35:50,320 --> 00:35:52,640
Come on, step in.

501
00:35:53,000 --> 00:35:54,000
She's your fan too.

502
00:35:55,200 --> 00:35:56,560
I dressed up for this.

503
00:35:57,240 --> 00:35:58,720
One, two, three.

504
00:36:00,280 --> 00:36:01,720
One, two, three.

505
00:36:02,640 --> 00:36:03,760
One, two.

506
00:36:03,960 --> 00:36:04,960
Okay.

507
00:36:11,040 --> 00:36:12,040
Raffy.

508
00:36:12,400 --> 00:36:15,560
Next time, if you don't
want to come, just tell her.

509
00:36:17,720 --> 00:36:18,800
I have to.

510
00:36:19,440 --> 00:36:20,560
It's a family show.

511
00:36:21,800 --> 00:36:23,200
Are you trying to dig something up?

512
00:36:23,800 --> 00:36:25,160
I'm not digging up anything.

513
00:36:26,240 --> 00:36:27,240
But…

514
00:36:29,350 --> 00:36:30,785
You do like to brag.

515
00:36:31,240 --> 00:36:33,320
You told your mom
you got the lead role in the play.

516
00:36:38,120 --> 00:36:39,120
I didn't tell her.

517
00:36:39,740 --> 00:36:41,260
She just filled in the blanks herself.

518
00:36:46,193 --> 00:36:48,113
I never told my mom I had the lead.

519
00:36:49,040 --> 00:36:51,639
I know I'm just a supporting character.

520
00:36:51,640 --> 00:36:55,360
Hey, I didn't mean it like that.

521
00:36:55,800 --> 00:36:57,280
And I'm not blaming you for anything.

522
00:36:58,240 --> 00:36:59,400
I'm just telling the truth.

523
00:37:00,840 --> 00:37:02,040
I only got a supporting role.

524
00:37:02,680 --> 00:37:04,960
And no matter what I do,
my mom will never be proud of me.

525
00:37:06,840 --> 00:37:09,240
That's why I didn't want to come.

526
00:37:16,960 --> 00:37:19,640
Then next time, just tell her
you don't want to come.

527
00:37:19,840 --> 00:37:20,840
What's she gonna do?

528
00:37:31,840 --> 00:37:34,440
Hey, trust me.

529
00:37:35,360 --> 00:37:37,560
I've pulled every kind of
stubborn stunt with my family.

530
00:37:38,000 --> 00:37:41,280
If you insist on saying no,
what can anyone do to you?

531
00:37:50,120 --> 00:37:52,239
Come on. Clean off
your makeup and change.

532
00:37:52,240 --> 00:37:53,360
I'll take you back.

533
00:38:02,800 --> 00:38:04,719
Come on, guys. Let's cheers!

534
00:38:04,720 --> 00:38:06,280
- Come on, guys. Let's cheers!
- Cheers!

535
00:38:10,320 --> 00:38:11,440
Listen.

536
00:38:12,480 --> 00:38:17,480
Our backdrop isn't empty anymore
because we've got a sponsor!

537
00:38:19,120 --> 00:38:20,999
Nice work, Timmy.

538
00:38:21,000 --> 00:38:23,640
But the money you got
only covers the stage set.

539
00:38:23,760 --> 00:38:25,240
It doesn't include the costumes yet.

540
00:38:25,560 --> 00:38:26,560
What?

541
00:38:26,960 --> 00:38:29,120
It's just the first step, dude.

542
00:38:29,400 --> 00:38:32,160
We should be happy
with the small wins first.

543
00:38:33,000 --> 00:38:35,200
I'll pitch more sponsors later.

544
00:38:35,560 --> 00:38:38,120
I'm not letting our
actors go on stage naked.

545
00:38:39,120 --> 00:38:41,920
As for you, Jack. Don't be stubborn.

546
00:38:42,800 --> 00:38:44,840
We have to show the sponsor's logo.

547
00:38:45,160 --> 00:38:48,800
The size is exactly
what they asked for. Okay?

548
00:38:49,360 --> 00:38:50,360
Okay.

549
00:38:52,097 --> 00:38:53,720
Ooh! Put it here.

550
00:38:54,280 --> 00:38:57,120
Bring us another bottle of whiskey.
Tell Pink to put it on Jack's tab.

551
00:38:57,280 --> 00:38:59,160
Tonight, it's Jack's treat.

552
00:38:59,320 --> 00:39:00,320
Cheers!

553
00:39:01,880 --> 00:39:03,480
Look how happy you are.

554
00:39:03,920 --> 00:39:07,199
I think the 50K we got today
is going straight into tonight's drinks.

555
00:39:07,200 --> 00:39:08,360
Tua won't get a share.

556
00:39:09,160 --> 00:39:10,160
Of course, he will.

557
00:39:10,161 --> 00:39:11,200
Right, Tua?

558
00:39:16,880 --> 00:39:17,880
Tua.

559
00:39:19,400 --> 00:39:20,400
Tua.

560
00:39:20,520 --> 00:39:21,520
Hey.

561
00:39:24,080 --> 00:39:25,080
Is something wrong?

562
00:39:26,360 --> 00:39:27,040
Nothing.

563
00:39:27,041 --> 00:39:28,640
Then let's cheers.

564
00:39:32,720 --> 00:39:34,120
Just let me know if something's up.

565
00:39:36,360 --> 00:39:37,960
I'm gonana use the bathroom.

566
00:39:38,640 --> 00:39:39,280
Don't take too long.
Yeah.

567
00:39:44,240 --> 00:39:45,240
Here.

568
00:39:53,680 --> 00:39:55,240
Do you model often?

569
00:39:56,240 --> 00:39:57,240
This is my first time.

570
00:39:57,920 --> 00:39:59,600
I've always wondered what it's like.

571
00:40:00,720 --> 00:40:03,880
If you're ready, take off your shirt.
I'll set up the camera.

572
00:40:42,800 --> 00:40:43,800
How should I pose?

573
00:40:47,560 --> 00:40:50,240
However you like.
Any pose you feel comfortable with.

574
00:40:56,800 --> 00:40:57,800
We'll start now.

575
00:41:24,760 --> 00:41:29,360
If I grab your ass once,
how much will that cost, James Dean?

576
00:41:30,960 --> 00:41:33,840
If you're so desperate to grab an ass,
why don't you try your dad's?

577
00:41:34,840 --> 00:41:35,960
Whoa, you prick.

578
00:41:39,880 --> 00:41:40,920
Aren't you a hooker?

579
00:41:41,000 --> 00:41:42,000
I'm not.

580
00:41:42,160 --> 00:41:43,280
I'm just a host.

581
00:41:43,720 --> 00:41:47,520
And if I were selling myself, I wouldn't
sell it to some ugly asshole like you.

582
00:41:48,120 --> 00:41:49,120
Mouthy, aren't you?

583
00:41:55,880 --> 00:41:58,080
Ugly face and an ugly personality too,
you motherfucker!

584
00:41:59,320 --> 00:42:00,320
Let go of me!

585
00:42:01,200 --> 00:42:02,376
What the hell are you guys doing?

586
00:42:02,400 --> 00:42:03,400
Son of a bitch!

587
00:42:06,920 --> 00:42:09,280
I was negotiating with a host.
Why the fuck did you butt in?

588
00:42:09,400 --> 00:42:10,400
So you're not gonna stop?

589
00:42:10,600 --> 00:42:11,600
Got a problem?

590
00:42:11,640 --> 00:42:12,200
Just go.
Let's leave.

591
00:42:38,240 --> 00:42:39,240
Hey.

592
00:42:39,760 --> 00:42:42,240
Aren't Jack and Dean
coming back to the table?

593
00:42:43,160 --> 00:42:44,680
I gotta go. There's an emergency.

594
00:42:45,120 --> 00:42:46,120
What?!

595
00:42:46,760 --> 00:42:48,200
You're leaving too?

596
00:42:48,960 --> 00:42:49,960
Tua!

597
00:42:51,960 --> 00:42:53,160
Fine, I'll drink alone.

598
00:42:58,040 --> 00:42:59,960
Ouch. Jack, that hurts.

599
00:43:01,920 --> 00:43:04,720
I see you don't like
being the lead in a romantic play.

600
00:43:04,960 --> 00:43:06,640
You'd rather be the lead in an action one.

601
00:43:09,040 --> 00:43:12,040
Thanks a lot anyway.

602
00:43:12,600 --> 00:43:17,120
Without you, I'd have been
outnumbered and beaten up.

603
00:43:21,200 --> 00:43:22,680
I won't let anything happen to you.

604
00:43:23,840 --> 00:43:26,040
Besides, those guys were real assholes.

605
00:43:27,000 --> 00:43:28,000
True.

606
00:43:29,560 --> 00:43:34,120
If someone like me is going to get groped,
I should at least get paid for it.

607
00:43:36,440 --> 00:43:37,959
You've still got the nerve
to joke about it, huh?

608
00:43:37,960 --> 00:43:40,160
Ouch, Jack. It hurts.

609
00:43:50,320 --> 00:43:51,360
What can I do?

610
00:43:52,120 --> 00:43:53,520
I can't change my past.

611
00:43:54,960 --> 00:43:57,640
All I can do is decide how to deal with it.

612
00:43:59,640 --> 00:44:00,976
From now on, I'm not going to be afraid.

613
00:44:01,000 --> 00:44:04,520
If someone tries to pick a fight,
I'll freaking fight back.

614
00:44:26,040 --> 00:44:29,680
When I said I wanted to change,

615
00:44:34,120 --> 00:44:35,360
I meant it.

616
00:44:38,200 --> 00:44:39,560
I want to be the new Dean for you.

617
00:44:48,560 --> 00:44:49,560
Do you still love me?

618
00:45:01,280 --> 00:45:02,840
I don't want to throw that word around.

619
00:45:05,680 --> 00:45:07,000
But I really want to hear…

620
00:45:10,200 --> 00:45:11,480
if you still love me or not.

621
00:45:33,320 --> 00:45:34,320
You got your answer?

622
00:45:35,840 --> 00:45:36,840
Mm.

623
00:45:57,640 --> 00:45:59,120
How long have you and Tua been close?

624
00:46:00,080 --> 00:46:00,800
Quite long.

625
00:46:01,000 --> 00:46:02,000
Since our first year.

626
00:46:03,240 --> 00:46:04,840
You two don't look like you're friends.

627
00:46:06,160 --> 00:46:07,200
Looks like something else.

628
00:46:13,480 --> 00:46:17,680
Actually, I came to see you today
because I wanted to talk about that.

629
00:46:21,280 --> 00:46:22,600
Stop making Tua uncomfortable.

630
00:46:23,680 --> 00:46:24,760
Tua doesn't like you.

631
00:46:28,440 --> 00:46:29,440
Why?

632
00:46:30,280 --> 00:46:31,280
Do you like him?

633
00:46:35,920 --> 00:46:36,920
I'm not sure.

634
00:46:39,120 --> 00:46:40,520
That's not a good enough answer.

635
00:46:41,383 --> 00:46:43,053
If you're not sure, you'd better back off.

636
00:46:44,059 --> 00:46:47,419
I feel good about him,
and I care about him a lot.

637
00:46:48,666 --> 00:46:50,386
Even if I'm not sure about my feelings yet,

638
00:46:51,640 --> 00:46:57,280
I'm sure someone like Tua
is too good for you.

639
00:46:59,040 --> 00:47:02,520
And how are you so sure
Tua doesn't have feelings for me?

640
00:47:09,880 --> 00:47:13,880
And if I leave him alone,
what do I get out of it?

641
00:47:19,440 --> 00:47:21,600
If you've got something better to offer me…

642
00:47:26,600 --> 00:47:27,760
I might change my mind.

643
00:47:34,800 --> 00:47:35,800
What are you two doing?

644
00:47:37,920 --> 00:47:39,960
Whoa. You really came all this way?

645
00:47:40,840 --> 00:47:43,080
Are you afraid I might
do something to your close friend?

646
00:47:46,720 --> 00:47:47,720
And what are you doing?

647
00:47:50,080 --> 00:47:53,480
I'm not doing anything. We're just talking.

648
00:47:53,680 --> 00:47:54,680
Right?

649
00:47:56,800 --> 00:47:58,000
Arnold's worried about you.

650
00:47:58,320 --> 00:47:59,680
He wants me to stay away from you.

651
00:48:01,080 --> 00:48:03,280
What did you say just now, Arnold?

652
00:48:03,699 --> 00:48:04,979
How do you feel about Tua again?

653
00:48:10,000 --> 00:48:11,000
I…

654
00:48:13,713 --> 00:48:15,313
What exactly were you two talking about?

655
00:48:15,800 --> 00:48:16,800
About me?

656
00:48:24,920 --> 00:48:26,440
Well, you've had my attention lately.

657
00:48:27,680 --> 00:48:29,040
Who else would I be talking about?

658
00:49:04,320 --> 00:49:05,560
Leave Tua alone.

659
00:49:21,760 --> 00:49:23,839
(Next Episode)
Timmy and I spoke with the sponsor.

660
00:49:23,840 --> 00:49:25,759
They wanted leads with a large following.

661
00:49:25,784 --> 00:49:28,309
So they suggested Raffy
take the lead role too.

662
00:49:28,334 --> 00:49:29,969
Even though we
had a fair casting…

663
00:49:30,000 --> 00:49:32,235
Why are you stealing
the lead role from me?

664
00:49:32,260 --> 00:49:32,739
What the hell are you talking about?

665
00:49:32,764 --> 00:49:33,879
Are you playing dumb?

666
00:49:33,904 --> 00:49:34,728
Why were you drinking alone?
I was bored…

667
00:49:35,794 --> 00:49:36,574
needed something to kill time.

668
00:49:36,841 --> 00:49:37,914
I can accompany you.

669
00:49:39,864 --> 00:49:41,577
I don't really have an answer.

670
00:49:41,602 --> 00:49:43,234
I don't even know
what this feeling is…

671
00:49:43,259 --> 00:49:44,507
But I like you, Arnold.
